<div class="post-content">

<h2>New Worlds to Explore</h2>
<p>FNAF World Refreshed doesn't just polish what was already there — it adds entirely new areas to discover, each with unique enemies, bosses, and environmental mechanics.</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Ice Caves:</strong> A scrapped area from the original FNAF World that Team Refresh restored and fully fleshed out. It's home to powerful chips and a boss inspired by Freddy Frostbear.</li>
    <li><strong>Backwoods:</strong> A jungle-swamp biome with original enemies and bosses, including Salvage and Dreadbear as a rare random encounter.</li>
    <li><strong>Withering Dunes:</strong> A western-themed desert zone with an environmental mechanic that gradually drains your party's health. Features completely original enemy designs, a cameo from Pan Stan, and a boss fight against the Mad Coyote. Widely considered the most visually impressive area in the game.</li>
</ul>

<p>The overworld itself has been improved too — diagonal movement, faster speed in the Flipside, NPCs with flavor dialogue, training dummies to test attacks, and redesigned puzzles that are far less tedious than the originals. The game now has 10 explorable worlds in total.</p>

</div>

