<div class="post-content">

<h2>20+ New Characters, Skins, and Minigames</h2>
<p>The roster has been massively expanded with over 20 new playable characters pulled from across the entire FNAF franchise: Golden Freddy (Withered), Candy Cadet, Dreadbear, Salvage, Phone Guy, Sparky the Dog, Lolbit, the Rockstar animatronics, Lefty, Helpy, and many more. Each one has a unique moveset and a defined class, and every unlocked character appears as an NPC on the map with their own dialogue.</p>

<p>Unlocking them is half the fun. Lolbit requires collecting all bytes. Mendo appears as a boss after maxing out defense upgrades. DD is caught by fishing up a pearl with a hat. Nightmare Mangle demands a C-rank in Foxy Fighters. These aren't just handed to you — they're rewards for exploring and mastering the game's systems.</p>

<h3>Skins</h3>
<p>A ticket-based skin system lets you customize characters with alternate looks pulled from FNAF AR, fan designs, hoaxes, memes, and even other fangames like Day Shift at Freddy's. Tickets are earned through minigames hosted at Candy Cadet's Tent.</p>

<h3>Minigames</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Endless Mode:</strong> Survive 30 waves of combat. Completing it unlocks Candy Cadet as a playable character.</li>
    <li><strong>Find Willie:</strong> Hunt for Purple Guy in 8-bit landscapes against a timer.</li>
    <li><strong>Bonnie's Jam:</strong> A rhythm game featuring fan-made FNAF songs, styled after Friday Night Funkin'.</li>
    <li><strong>Freddy in Space:</strong> A complete remake of the original minigame, rebuilt as a Mega Man-style platformer with dashing, crouching, aiming, and a super move.</li>
</ul>

</div>

